issue.title: 502 error code after update to 1.20.1
issue.body:
- MSSQL Extension Version: 1.20.1
- VSCode Version: 1.80.1
- OS Version: Win11

This is a continuation of the [getProxyAgentOptions error](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/issues/17755#top) error I previously reported.

I was able to get version 1.20.0 working using the advise at https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/issues/17755#issuecomment-1657959401

After VSCode updated the extension to 1.20.1 today, when I try to establish a SQL Connection I now get a 502 error: 


```
Installing SQL tools service to c:\Users\EVCallahan\.vscode\extensions\ms-mssql.mssql-1.20.1\sqltoolsservice\4.8.1.2\Windows.
Downloading https://github.com/Microsoft/sqltoolsservice/releases/download/4.8.1.2/microsoft.sqltools.servicelayer-win-x64-net7.0.zip
failed (error code '502')
[ERROR] Error: 502
```

Manually downloading https://github.com/Microsoft/sqltoolsservice/releases/download/4.8.1.2/microsoft.sqltools.servicelayer-win-x64-net7.0.zip and extracting the content to C:\Users\\<username\>\\.vscode\extensions\ms-mssql.mssql-1.20.1\sqltoolsservice\4.8.1.2\Windows and restarting VSCode worked around the problem





Steps to Reproduce:

1. Allow VSCode to update mssql extension from 1.20.0 to 1.20.1
2. Try to establish SQL Connection with mssql.connect



![image](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/assets/42499434/dc74d86f-ccb5-4190-9fa0-a312949b1b4a)

pull_request.title: Remove HttpClient and Proxy agent options completely
pull_request.body:
Build over PR #17809 to fix https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/issues/17772

Specifying proxy URL in http.proxy settings in VS Code is causing URL resolution issues as VS Code gets smarter to resolve proxy when accessing URLs, and is related with all the changes we also made in ADS for the same. ref. PRs: 
https://github.com/microsoft/azuredatastudio/pull/24549
https://github.com/microsoft/azuredatastudio/pull/24118

pull_request.title: Rename Azure AD to Microsoft Entra Id
pull_request.body:
Fixes #17824 

Below public APIs are affected: 

1. Renamed commands are below:
(NOTE: Command Ids are unchanged to prevent breaking changes)

      | Command Id | Before | After (new) |
      | -------------- | -------- | ------------ |
      | `mssql.addAadAccount` | "Add Azure Account" | "Add Microsoft Entra Account" |
      | `mssql.removeAadAccount` | "Remove Azure Account" | "Remove Microsoft Entra Account" |
      | `mssql.clearAzureAccountTokenCache` | "Clear Azure account token cache" | "Clear Microsoft Entra account token cache" |

Display changes:

![image](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/assets/13396919/81397a92-1a13-45bf-829b-95ee1d1ed9d3)

![image](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode-mssql/assets/13396919/687dcf84-059b-4c76-8fd3-abe988447bea)

Additionally error messages and prompts are updated to reflect new terminology.

issue.title: Copy results to clipboard does not work
issue.body:
- MSSQL Extension Version: 0.2.1
- VSCode Version: 1.9.0
- OS Version: ubuntu 16.04 LTS

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Execute any query
2. Select any from the results table
3. Press Ctrl+C (or click on "Copy" or click on "Copy with Headers" in the context menu)

Expected behavior: The selected Text was copied to the clipboard

Actually behavior: Nothing was copied to the clipboard. (Also, the current content of the clipboard is still there.)

comment.body:
I have a little different problem but related to copy data from RESULTS window. If I using mouse and context menu to copy something from RESULTS, it works well but when I want to use keyboard shortcuts there I can not copy any data from there. On query window it works.

VSCODE: 1.83.1
Extension: v1.21.0
